def: A cruciferrous plant (Hesperis matronalis), remarkable for itsfragrance, especially toward the close of the day; -- called alsorocket and dame's violet. Loudon.
Smoky; hence, fond of smoking; addicted to smoking tobacco.
Intellectual powers; possession of intellect; quality of beingintellectual.
Of, pertaining to, or designating, a vanadic acid analogous tometaphosphoric acid.
A rubbing or kneading of the body, especially when performed asa hygienic or remedial measure.
An oily liquid hydrocarbon extracted from the creosote ofbeechwood tar. It consists essentially of certain derivatives ofpyrogallol.
An inclined road in a coal mine, on which loaded cars descendby gravity, drawing up empty ones. Knight.
